cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the generation and control of filters for image recognition and quality assessment, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of unsupervised learning and the focus on interpretability suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The weighting of filters based on local structures may involve neural networks (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM) techniques.
